<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Conservation District (CD) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means a subdivision of a State organized pursuant to an applicable State Conservation 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
District law or in instances where a CD does not exist, the State Conservationist of the Soil Conservation Service.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Cost-share payment 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the payment made by ASCS to producers who complete an approved program practice. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
County committee (COC) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the Agricultural Stabilization and Conservation county committee of the ASCS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
County Conservation Review Group (CCRG) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
consists of the county ASC committee; the county extension agent; a Soil Conservation Service (SCS) representative;
a Forest Service (FS) representative; a Farmers Home Administration representative; a representative of the State
forestry agency or its equivalent, when the representative accepts an invitation to be a member of the group; and a
representative of the CD in the county, where the governing board of the district accepts an invitation to designate
a representative (if there is more than one district in the county, the governing boards of the districts may jointly
designate one person to represent all the districts). The CCRG shall have the responsibilities as provided for in
&sect;&sect;701.107 and 701.307. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
CPO 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the conservation plan of operations developed for the participant by the SCS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Deputy Administrator 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the Deputy Administrator, State and County Operations, or designee, of the ASCS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
ECP 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the Emergency Conservation Program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Eligible person 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means a person who meets all program eligibility requirements and is eligible to participate and receive assistance.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Farm or ranch 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means that area of land considered as a farm under the regulations governing reconstitution of farms, allotments,
and bases, at part 719 of this chapter, as amended, for ACP, ECP, and WQIP, and, for the FIP, farm or ranch means eligible
land (or ownership tracts) as provided in &sect;701.302. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
FIP 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the Forestry Incentives Program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
FS 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the Forest Service of the United States Department of Agriculture. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Incentive payment 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means, unless the context indicates otherwise, the incentive payment specified in the WQIP agreement which, subject
to the availability of funds, is made to a participant to compensate such participant who implemented conservation
practices or management changes that reduce agricultural pollutants. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
National Conservation Review Group (NCRG) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
consists of representatives of the ASCS; SCS; U.S. Forest Service; Extension Service; Economic Research Service;
Farmers Home Administration; Agricultural Research Service; Office of General Counsel, U.S. Department of Agriculture;
Office of Budget, Planning and Analysis, U.S. Department of Agriculture; Environmental Protection Agency; Office
of Management and Budget; and Fish and Wildlife Service, U.S. Department of the Interior (DOI). The NCRG is responsible
for recommending changes to the Administrator, ASCS, in program administrative procedures and policy guidelines,
and evaluations of program effectiveness and operating arrangements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Participant 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means an owner, operator, landlord, tenant, or sharecropper of a farm or ranch who shares in the cost of the practice
and who will receive cost-share or incentive assistance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Program year 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the Federal fiscal year for accounting purposes. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
SCS 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the Soil Conservation Service of the United States Department of Agriculture. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means any one State of the United States, Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands, and: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) In the case of the ACP and ECP, Guam, the American Samoa, and the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands; and

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) In the case of the FIP, Guam, the American Samoa, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, the Trust Territory
of the Pacific Islands and the territories and possessions of the United States. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State committee (STC) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the ASCS State Agricultural Stabilization and Conservation Committee. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State Conservation Review Group (SCRG) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
consists of the STC, the State Director of Extension; the State Conservationist of the SCS; a representative of the
U.S. Forest Service; a representative of the Farmers Home Administration; a representative of the State forestry
agency, or its equivalent, when the representative accepts an invitation to be a member of the group; a representative
of the State Soil Conservation Committee, or its equivalent, when the representative accepts an invitation to be
a member of the group; and a representative of the State water quality agency, or its equivalent when it accepts an invitation
to be a member of the group. The SCRG has the responsibility provided for in &sect;701.108. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State Forestry Committee, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
or its equivalent, consists of the State forester or equivalent State official, who serves as chairperson; and a representative
at the State level of the following USDA agencies: ASCS; FS; Extension Service; Farmers Home Administration; and
SCS. At the discretion of the State Forestry Committee, State and local interests may also be involved. The function
of the State Forestry Committee is to coordinate forestry budget proposals, agency roles in education, technical
assistance, technology transfers, and forestry incentives. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

