<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
long-term requirement, as required by proposed &sect;960.5 (a)(1) and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The Bank's requirements for and verification procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
concerning (i) the use of subsidized advances or direct subsidies 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
within a reasonable period of time after approval of an AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application, as required by proposed &sect;960.12(a), or (ii) the use of loans or grants within a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
reasonable period of time after repayment of such funds to a loan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
fund or loan consortium, as required by proposed &sect;960.17(c)(5); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The Bank's verification procedures upon initial 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
disbursement of subsidized advances or direct subsidies, as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
required by proposed &sect;960.13; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) The Bank's monitoring plan, as required by proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;960.14(b); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) The Bank's reporting requirements for applicants during the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
construction or rehabilitation phase, as required by proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;960.15(b)(2); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) An explanation of circumstances justifying undue hardship 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
waivers by the Bank of imposition of remedial actions, as required 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
by proposed &sect;960.16 (c)(1) and (d)(1); and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) The Bank's determination regarding the number of persons 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that may serve on the Bank's Advisory Council and their terms, as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
required by proposed &sect;960.21(a)(1) and (4). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.2(c) of the proposed rule provides that the Bank's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed AHP implementation plan shall be submitted to its 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Advisory Council at least 45 calendar days before it is considered 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
by the Bank's board of directors. The Advisory Council shall 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
review the proposed plan and submit its recommendations to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank's board of directors at least seven calendar days before the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank's board of directors is scheduled to vote on the proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
plan. The Bank's board of directors shall vote on the proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP implementation plan, and shall submit its approved plan to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Board for action. The Board shall approve or disapprove the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed plan within 60 calendar days of receipt. The Bank's plan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is not effective until it is approved by the Board, and it must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
become effective at least 45 calendar days before the due date for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP applications established by the Bank. Each Bank must submit 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
its AHP implementation plan to the Board for approval no later 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
than 180 calendar days after the publication of this rule as a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
final rule in the 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Federal Register
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.2(d) of the proposed rule provides that the Bank's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approved AHP implementation plan shall be made available by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank to the public upon request. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.2(e) of the proposed rule provides that the Board 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
will approve or disapprove proposed amendments to a Bank's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approved AHP implementation plan submitted by the Bank within 60 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
calendar days of receipt. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
C. Authorized and Required Uses of AHP Subsidized Advances or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Direct Subsidies 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 960.3 of the proposed rule states the general 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
authorized uses of AHP subsidized advances and direct subsidies by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicants, &sect;960.4 provides specific examples of such authorized 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and unauthorized uses and other use requirements, and &sect;960.5 sets 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
forth the long-term income-eligibility, affordability and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
income-targeting requirements for such uses. These proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sections are discussed further below. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
1. Authorized Uses of Subsidized Advances or Direct 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Subsidies 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 960.3 of the proposed rule, consistent with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;960.3(b) (1) and (2) of the Board's existing AHP regulation, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provides that applicants may use subsidized advances or direct 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subsidies received from a Bank under the AHP to either: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Finance the purchase, construction or rehabilitation of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
owner-occupied housing units by or for low- or moderate-income 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
households; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Finance the purchase, construction or rehabilitation of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rental housing units, at least 20 percent of the units of which 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
will be occupied by and affordable for very low-income households. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
See 12 CFR 960.3(b) (1) and (2). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
2. Specific Use Requirements for Subsidized Advances or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Direct Subsidies 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 960.3(c) of the Board's existing AHP regulation 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provides that ``Program funds may only be used for direct costs 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
required to produce and/or finance affordable housing units.'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
12 CFR 960.3(c). A number of questions have arisen as to whether 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
specific types of costs associated with the financing or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
production of housing may be considered ``direct costs'' for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
purposes of the Board's regulation. Because of the confusion in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this area, the Board believes that it would be helpful to set 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
forth in the rule examples of specific types of costs it considers 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to be authorized and unauthorized for AHP purposes. Accordingly, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;960.4(a) (1) and (2) of the proposed rule sets forth examples of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
specific costs related to the purchase, construction or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rehabilitation of housing that are authorized and unauthorized 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
uses of AHP subsidized advances or direct subsidies. However, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
because it is impossible to anticipate all types of costs that may 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
arise in the course of financing or producing housing, the list of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
authorized and unauthorized costs in proposed &sect;960.4(a) is not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
exclusive. Other costs not included arguably may or may not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
qualify as costs of financing the purchase, construction or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rehabilitation of housing. If an applicant seeks to use funds 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under the AHP to pay for costs not specifically included in this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rule, it should consult with the Bank before submitting its 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application for approval. The Board specifically asks for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
comments as to whether these authorized and unauthorized costs are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
appropriate. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
