The Board's existing AHP regulation defines ``low- and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
moderate-income households'' as households for which the aggregate 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
income is 80 percent or less of the area median income, and ``very 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
low-income households'' as households for which the aggregate 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
income is 50 percent or less of the area median income. See 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
12 CFR 960.1(g), (o). ``Median income'' is defined as ``the median 
