Proposed &sect;960.5(a)(1) implements section 10(j)(2)(B) of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Act, which provides that Bank members may use subsidized advances 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
received from the Banks to finance the purchase, construction, or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rehabilitation of rental housing, at least 20 percent of the units 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of which will be occupied by and affordable for very low-income 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
households for the remaining useful life of such housing or the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
mortgage term. 12 U.S.C. 1430(j)(2)(B). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Proposed &sect;960.5(a)(1) provides that the applicant and project 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sponsor shall state in the AHP application their commitment 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
regarding satisfaction of the long-term income-eligibility, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affordability and income-targeting requirements. In addition, an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicant may commit to maintain additional units as affordable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for and occupied by low- or moderate-income households, which 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
commitment shall be a minimum period of 30 years or, at the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
election of the sponsor, the remaining useful life of such units. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 
