<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
D. Establishment of AHP Funding Cycles and Available AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Subsidies 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.6(a)(1) of the proposed rule requires each Bank to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
establish at least two but no more than four AHP funding cycles 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
per year during which applications for AHP subsidized advances or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
direct subsidies will be accepted. This is a change from the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Board's existing AHP regulation, which provides that the Banks may 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accept AHP applications during two of four quarterly periods each 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
year. See 12 CFR 960.4(a). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.6(a)(1) of the proposed rule also provides that the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP funding cycle schedule, including application due dates, is to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be determined by the Bank in its discretion, but shall allow for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sufficient time intervals to ensure an adequate pool of applicants 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to compete in each funding cycle. The funding cycles schedule, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
including application due dates, shall be described in detail in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Bank's AHP implementation plan. This is also a change from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Board's existing AHP regulation, which sets forth specific 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application due dates. See 12 CFR 960.4(a). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.6(a)(2) of the proposed rule provides that each 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank shall inform the general public and its members of the number 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and dates of its AHP funding cycles for the year and the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approximate amount of available AHP subsidies for each funding 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
cycle at least 45 calendar days before the due date for AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applications for the first funding cycle for the year. This is a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
change from the Board's existing AHP regulation, which requires 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
each Bank to announce its funding cycles by December 1 of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
preceding year, and to notify only its members of the approximate 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amount of AHP subsidies to be offered in each funding cycle. See 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
12 CFR 960.4(a), (b). 
