<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 960.7(b)(3) of the proposed rule provides that within 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
30 calendar days of each Bank's approval of the AHP applications 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for a given AHP funding cycle, the Bank shall forward to the Board 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a summary of each approved AHP application. The summary shall: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Briefly describe the project, including the applicant, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
loan fund or loan consortium, if applicable, and the sponsor_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
whether nonprofit, for-profit or public agency, the type of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
housing, the location, the long-term period committed to, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
number of housing units including the number of units affordable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for very low-, low- or moderate-income households or for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
households at any other income levels committed to in the AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application, the development cost, other financing sources, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
special needs populations served; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) State the reason for the points awarded under each of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank's scoring criteria for the project; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Indicate whether a subsidized advance or direct subsidy 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
was approved by the Bank for the project, the use of such funds, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and the amount of such funds approved; if a subsidized advance was 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approved, the summary shall indicate the amount of the advance, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the advance rate, the amortization schedule for the advance, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
term to maturity, the applicable cost of funds, and the date as of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
which the cost of funds was determined; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Indicate whether the project received approval in a prior 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP funding cycle, or whether the project is an extension, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
expansion, continuation or reconfiguration of a previously 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approved AHP project; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Describe how the project will be monitored and by what 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
entity; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi) Describe the legal mechanisms to be used to ensure 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliance by the project with the long-term requirement contained 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in &sect;960.5 of the proposed rule; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vii) Include a summary in chart form showing all AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applications received by the Bank in the particular AHP funding 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
cycle, with the score each application received for each scoring 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
criterion, and the total score received by each project; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(viii) Include any other information required by the Board. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Board has general oversight responsibility over the AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under section 10(j) of the Act. See 12 U.S.C. 1430(j). In 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
addition, section 10(j)(12)(A) of the Act requires the Board to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitor and report annually to the Congress and the Advisory 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Council for each Bank the support of low-income housing and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
community development by the Banks and the utilization of advances 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for these purposes. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Id. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;1430(j)(12)(A). Since the Board would 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
no longer be receiving and approving AHP applications under the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed rule, the Board would no longer have these applications 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as a source of data to assist the Board in exercising its 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
oversight and monitoring responsibilities and preparing the annual 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
report to the Congress and the Advisory Councils. Accordingly, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Board will need the Banks to provide this additional 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
information to the Board in the summary, as required in proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;960.7(b)(3). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
F. Requirements For Approval of AHP Applications 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
1. General 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 960.8(a) of the proposed rule provides that each Bank 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall evaluate the AHP applications received to determine if they 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
satisfy the threshold criteria in proposed &sect;960.9. All 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applications that meet the threshold criteria shall be scored 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
pursuant to the criteria contained in proposed &sect;960.10 as set 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
forth in the Bank's approved AHP implementation plan. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.8(b) of the proposed rule provides that the Bank 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall approve the applications in descending order starting with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the highest scoring application until the total AHP funding amount 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for the particular funding cycle, except for any amount 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
insufficient to fund the next highest scoring project, has been 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
allocated. The Bank also may approve the next four highest 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
scoring applications as alternates and, within one year of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approval by the Bank, may fund such alternates if any previously 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
committed AHP funds become available. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
2. Threshold Criteria for Approval of AHP Applications 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 960.9 of the proposed rule provides that an AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application must meet all of the threshold criteria set forth in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a. through f. below in order to be considered for scoring under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed &sect;960.10 and for AHP funding approval. These criteria 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
are discussed in detail below. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Authorized and required uses requirements. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application must indicate that the use of the subsidized advance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or direct subsidy set forth in the AHP application for the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed project will comply with the requirements for authorized 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and required uses of such funds contained in proposed &sect;&sect;960.3, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
960.4 and 960.5. See proposed &sect;960.9(a). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
This proposed provision is consistent with the intent of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;960.5(a)(1) of the Board's existing AHP regulation. See 12 CFR 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
960.5(a)(1). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
b. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Fair housing law requirements. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The AHP application must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
indicate that the project sponsor will comply with any applicable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
fair housing law requirements and must indicate how the sponsor 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposes to affirmatively further compliance with such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements. See proposed &sect;960.9(b). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
