the project pursuant to the AHP, the type and complexity of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
project, or other factors deemed relevant by the Bank. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
An alternative option would be to require that the Bank only 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would have to review land title records on a sample basis, as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determined by the Bank. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Rental housing projects. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.14(e)(2)(i) of the proposed rule provides that the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank shall require an AHP-assisted rental housing project to be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subject to a deed restriction or other legally enforceable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
mechanism which requires that upon sale of the project prior to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the end of the long-term period during which the project's rental 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
units, or portion thereof, must remain affordable for and occupied 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
by households with incomes at or below the level committed to in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the AHP application, the Bank or its designee must receive notice 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the sale, and: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The project's rental units, or portion thereof, must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
continue to be affordable for and occupied by households with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
incomes at or below the levels committed to in the AHP application 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for the remainder of the long-term period committed to in the AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application, and the purchaser agrees to be subject to the same 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
restrictions on resale that applied to the seller; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the purchaser does not satisfy the requirements in (1) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
above, and if the Bank provided a direct subsidy to the applicant 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
which was passed on as a grant to the seller, the seller must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
repay a pro rata portion of the grant to the applicant, as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provided in &sect;960.16(d)(1) of the proposed rule; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If the purchaser does not satisfy the requirements in (1) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
above, and if the Bank provided a subsidized advance to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicant which in turn provided a below market rate loan to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
seller, then the provisions of &sect;960.16(d)(2) shall apply. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.14(e)(2)(ii) of the proposed rule provides that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
upon initial full occupancy of the units in an AHP-assisted rental 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
housing project or one year after initial disbursement of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subsidized advance or direct subsidy, whichever occurs first, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank or its designee shall obtain a certification from the sponsor 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or the owner that the project's units, or portion thereof, are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affordable for and occupied by households with incomes at initial 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
occupancy at or below the levels committed to in the AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.14(e)(2)(iii)(A) of the proposed rule provides that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
during the long-term period for which the units, or portion 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
thereof, of a rental housing project must remain affordable for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and occupied by households with incomes at or below the levels 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
committed to in the AHP application, the Bank or its designee 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall monitor the project to determine whether the project's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
units, or portion thereof, remain affordable for and occupied by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
households with incomes at or below the levels committed to in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP application. The Board requests comments on several options 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for implementing this requirement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.14(e)(2)(iii)(B) of the proposed rule proposes that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitoring shall include, but is not limited to, periodic review 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of relevant household income and rent reports or certifications 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
obtained from the sponsor or the owner and, at least on a sample 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
basis, periodic inspections of the project at intervals to be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determined by the Bank, based on the amount of AHP assistance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
received by the project, the type and complexity of the project, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and other factors deemed relevant by the Bank. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

