<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Another option would be that where funds other than funds 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provided under the AHP are the predominant source of financing for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
an AHP-assisted rental housing project and the monitoring 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
activities of such other funding source are sufficient to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determine the project's compliance with the requirements of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP, as committed to in the AHP application, the monitoring 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirement would be deemed to be fulfilled. However, if the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitoring activities of such other funding source are not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sufficient to determine the project's compliance with the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements of the AHP, as committed to in the AHP application, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Bank would be required to monitor the project by conducting 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
inspections, at least on a sample basis, as determined by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank, based on the amount of the funds received by the project 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under the AHP, the type and complexity of the project, or other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
factors deemed relevant by the Bank. In the alternative, if the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitoring activities of such other funding source are not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sufficient to determine the project's compliance with the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements of the AHP, as committed to in the AHP application, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
could the Bank rely on monitoring activities of the predominant 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
funding source as long as it is monitoring for compliance with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements that are substantially similar to the AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Board specifically requests comments on how random sampling 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
could be used to monitor AHP-assisted rental housing projects to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determine whether, during the long-term period committed to in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP application, the project's units continue to be affordable for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and occupied by households with incomes at or below the levels 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
committed to in the AHP application. For example, sampling could 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
involve monitoring a portion of AHP-assisted rental projects at 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
fixed intervals. The sampling method could be devised so that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
each project is monitored at least once during the long-term 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
period committed to in the AHP application. Alternatively, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sampling method might be structured so that some, but not all, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP-assisted rental projects are monitored during the long-term 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
period committed to in the AHP application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Act requires that the AHP regulation must ensure that the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP will be used only to assist projects for which adequate 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
long-term monitoring is available to guarantee that affordability 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
standards and other requirements of the Act are satisfied. See 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
12 U.S.C. 1430(j)(9)(C). The Board requests comments as to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
whether it is appropriate to interpret this requirement in a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
manner that permits monitoring to be done by sampling that could 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
result in some AHP-assisted rental projects not being monitored 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
during the long-term period committed to in the AHP application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
In addition, the Board specifically requests comments on whether 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
there are sampling techniques that would ensure that each project 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is monitored in satisfaction of the monitoring requirement in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
b. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Monitoring of special needs projects.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.14(f) of the proposed rule sets forth the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements for monitoring a project that commits to meet a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
special need pursuant to proposed &sect;960.10(d)(3), either through 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
providing units for persons with a special need or through 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
providing a special service to occupants, as defined in the Bank's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP implementation plan. If an applicant commits to fund a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
project that provides owner-occupied or rental housing units for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
persons with a special need, as defined in the Bank's AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
implementation plan, &sect;960.14(f)(1) of the proposed rule requires 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Bank or its designee to obtain a certification from the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sponsor or the owner upon completion and occupancy of the project 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that the project's units, or portion thereof, are occupied by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
persons with such special need. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
If an applicant in its AHP application commits to fund a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
project that will provide a continuing special service to its 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
occupants, as defined in the Bank's AHP implementation plan, such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as child care, job training, medical care, or other services 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
designed to meet the special needs of occupants, then 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;960.14(f)(1) of the proposed rule provides that the Bank or its 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
designee shall obtain a certification from the sponsor or owner 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
upon completion and occupancy of the project that the special 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
service is being provided to the occupants, as committed to in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
AHP application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.14(f)(2) of the proposed rule provides that, where 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
an applicant in its AHP application commits to fund a housing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
project that will provide a continuing special service, the Bank 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or its designee shall monitor the project, as determined by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank in its AHP implementation plan, for at least one year from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the date of initial full occupancy of the project to verify that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the special service continues to be provided to the occupants, as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
committed to in the AHP application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

