<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 960.15(d) of the proposed rule provides that each Bank 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall require applicants or sponsors to provide such other reports 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to the Bank, in addition to the reports and documentation required 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
by &sect;960.15 of the proposed rule, as the Bank deems necessary in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
order to fulfill its monitoring obligations under &sect;960.14 of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed rule. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
K. Corrective and Remedial Actions for Fraud or Non-Compliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
With AHP Requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 10(j) of the Act is silent on what specific corrective 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and remedial actions should be imposed when there is fraud or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
non-compliance with the requirements of the AHP. See 12 U.S.C. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1430(j). Accordingly, the Board has the discretion to determine, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as a matter of policy, what those requirements should be. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Board's existing AHP regulation provides that, where funds 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provided under the AHP will not be or are no longer being used for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
their approved purposes, the amount of committed but unused 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subsidy or improperly used subsidy shall be recovered and made 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
available by the Bank for future AHP projects. See 12 CFR 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
960.8(a). The existing regulation requires the Bank, in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
recapturing such funds, to take any or all of the following 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
actions, without limitation on other remedies, in its discretion: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a. Reprice the advance at the interest rate charged to members 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
on non-subsidized advances of comparable type and maturity at the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
time of the original advance; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
b. Call the advance; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
c. Assess a prepayment fee; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
d. Require the member to reimburse the Bank for the amount of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the unused or improperly used subsidy on the advance or other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
assistance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Id. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;960.8(b). In addition, some Banks have adopted procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
