<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Under &sect;960.17(d)(2)(ii) of the proposed rule, if the Bank 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
contracts with the loan fund or loan consortium to meet the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitoring requirements in &sect;960.14(e) through (h) of the proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rule, the Bank shall require the loan fund or loan consortium to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitor the AHP-assisted housing units according to the monitoring 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements of &sect;960.14(e) through (h) of the proposed rule. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank also shall require the loan fund or loan consortium to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
require the sponsor or owner of the project to submit to the loan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
fund or loan consortium such reports and certifications as are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
required under &sect;960.15(c) of the proposed rule. In addition, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
loan fund or loan consortium shall report to the Bank any new loan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or grant made using repayments of loans by the borrower. If a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
loan fund or loan consortium receives loans or grants from an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicant pursuant to separate AHP funding cycles, the use of such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
funds must be reported separately. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The monitoring and reporting requirements in &sect;960.17(d) of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed rule are a change from the provisions on monitoring and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
reporting in the Board's existing policy guidelines, which require 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the applicant to monitor the loan fund or loan consortium and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
require the Bank to monitor the applicant. This change is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
intended to conform the monitoring and reporting requirements for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
projects involving loan funds or loan consortia with the proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitoring and reporting requirements applicable to AHP-assisted 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
housing projects generally under &sect;&sect;960.14 and 960.15 of this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed rule. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.17(e)(1) of the proposed rule provides that a loan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
fund or loan consortium receiving loans or grants from applicants 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
pursuant to the AHP and the project sponsors and owners receiving 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
loans or grants from loan funds or loan consortia are subject to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the corrective and remedial actions contained in &sect;960.16 of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed rule for fraud and non-compliance with respect to the AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.17(e)(2)(i) of the proposed rule provides that in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the event of a loan fund's or loan consortium's fraud or willful 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
non-compliance with respect to the requirements of this part, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
full amount of the AHP subsidy shall be recovered from the loan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
fund or loan consortium by the applicant and returned to the Bank, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or if previously agreed to by the Bank, shall be recovered by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank from the loan fund or loan consortium. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.17(e)(2)(ii) of the proposed rule requires an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicant that provides a loan or a grant to a loan fund or loan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consortium pursuant to the AHP to have in place either: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A legally binding agreement or other legally enforceable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
mechanism that permits the applicant to recover from the loan fund 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or loan consortium, in the event of fraud or willful 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
non-compliance by the loan fund or loan consortium with respect to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the AHP requirements, the full amount of the AHP subsidy; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the Bank agrees and such an agreement is legally 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
enforceable, a three-party agreement that includes the Bank, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicant, and the loan fund or loan consortium, that permits the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Bank to recover from the loan fund or loan consortium, in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
event of fraud or willful non-compliance by the loan fund or loan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consortium with respect to the AHP requirements, the full amount 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the AHP subsidy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 960.17(e)(3)(i) of the proposed rule provides that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the event of a sponsor's or owner's fraud or willful 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
non-compliance with respect to the AHP requirements, the full 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amount of the AHP subsidy shall be recovered by the loan fund or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
loan consortium from the sponsor or owner to be used for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
additional AHP projects. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

