Subpart B_Establishment of AHP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;960.2 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Bank establishment of AHP and adoption of AHP implementation plan. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) It is the policy of the Board and the Banks to promote decent and safe affordable housing and to address critical
affordable housing needs through providing subsidized advances and direct subsidies to members pursuant to this
part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Each Bank's board of directors shall establish an AHP, which shall be funded pursuant to the requirements of &sect;960.18.
The Bank shall make subsidized advances to applicants pursuant to its AHP and shall operate its AHP in conformity with
an annual AHP implementation plan and the requirements of this part. Direct subsidies provided by a Bank to applicants
pursuant to its AHP shall be provided in conformity with the Bank's AHP implementation plan and the requirements of
this part. Each Bank's AHP implementation plan shall be approved by the Board before it is effective. The Bank's AHP
implementation plan shall meet the requirements of this part, and shall include: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The Bank's AHP funding cycle schedule, including application due dates, as required by &sect;960.6(a)(1); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Bank's priorities, and scoring criteria for applications, as required by &sect;&sect;960.8(a) and 960.10;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The Bank's procedures to ensure satisfaction of the long-term requirement, as required by &sect;960.5 (a)(1)
and (b); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The Bank's requirements for and verification procedures concerning: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The use of subsidized advances or direct subsidies within a reasonable period of time after approval of an AHP application,
as required by &sect;960.12(a); or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The use of loans or grants within a reasonable period of time after repayment of such funds to a loan fund or loan
consortium, as required by &sect;960.17(c)(5); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The Bank's verification procedures upon initial disbursement of subsidized advances or direct subsidies, as
required by &sect;960.13; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) The Bank's monitoring plan, as required by &sect;960.14(b); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) The Bank's reporting requirements for applicants during the construction or rehabilitation phase, as required
by &sect;960.15(b)(2); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) An explanation of circumstances justifying undue hardship waivers by the Bank of imposition of remedial actions,
as required by &sect;960.16 (c)(1) and (d)(1); and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) The Bank's determination regarding the number of persons that may serve on the Bank's Advisory Council and their
terms, as required by &sect;960.21(a) (1) and (4). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The Bank's proposed AHP implementation plan shall be submitted to its Advisory Council at least 45 calendar days
before it is considered by the Bank's board of directors. The Advisory Council shall review the proposed AHP implementation
plan and submit its recommendations to the Bank's board of directors at least seven calendar days before the Bank's
board of directors is scheduled to vote on the AHP implementation plan. The Bank's board of directors shall vote on
the proposed AHP implementation plan, and shall submit its approved plan to the Board for action. The Board shall approve
or disapprove any proposed AHP implementation plan it receives within 60 calendar days of receipt. A Bank's AHP implementation
plan must be effective at least 45 calendar days before the due date for AHP applications. Each Bank shall submit its
AHP implementation plan to the Board for approval no later than 180 calendar days after [the publication of the final
rule in the 
