<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(C) Report to the Bank any new loan or grant made using the repayments of loans by the borrower. If a loan fund or loan consortium
receives loans or grants from an applicant pursuant to separate AHP funding cycles, the use of such funds must be reported
separately. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Corrective and remedial actions for fraud or non-compliance with AHP requirements. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) A loan fund or loan consortium receiving loans or grants from an applicant pursuant to the AHP and the project sponsors
or owners receiving loans or grants from a loan fund or loan consortium are subject to the corrective and remedial actions
contained in &sect;960.16 for fraud and non-compliance with respect to the requirements of this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2)(i) In the event of a loan fund's or loan consortium's fraud or willful non-compliance with respect to the requirements
of this part, the full amount of the AHP subsidy shall be recovered from the loan fund or loan consortium by the applicant
and returned to the Bank or, if previously agreed to by the Bank, shall be recovered by the Bank from the loan fund or loan
consortium. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) An applicant that provides loans or grants to a loan fund or loan consortium pursuant to the AHP shall have in place
either: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) A legally binding agreement or other legally enforceable mechanism that permits it to recover from the loan fund
or loan consortium, in the event of fraud or willful non-compliance by the loan fund or loan consortium with respect
to the requirements of this part, the full amount of the AHP subsidy; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) If the Bank agrees and such an agreement is legally enforceable, a three-party agreement that includes the Bank,
the applicant and the loan fund or loan consortium that permits the Bank to recover from the loan fund or loan consortium,
in the event of fraud or willful non-compliance by the loan fund or loan consortium with respect to the requirements
of this part, the full amount of the AHP subsidy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3)(i) In the event of a sponsor's or owner's fraud or willful non-compliance with respect to the requirements of this
part, the full amount the AHP subsidy shall be recovered by the loan fund or loan consortium from the sponsor or owner,
to be used for additional AHP projects. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii)(A) The loan fund or loan consortium shall have in place a legally binding agreement or other legally enforceable
mechanism that permits it to recover from the sponsor or owner the full amount of the AHP subsidy provided to the project
in the event of the sponsor's or owner's fraud or willful non-compliance with respect to the requirements of this part,
and the applicant shall have in place a legally binding agreement or other legally enforceable mechanism that permits
it to recover from the loan fund or loan consortium such amount recovered by the loan fund or loan consortium from the
sponsor or owner; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The applicant shall have in place, if the Bank agrees and such agreement is legally enforceable, a four-party agreement
that includes the Bank, the applicant, the loan fund or loan consortium and the sponsor or owner, that permits the Bank
to recover from the sponsor or owner the full amount of the AHP subsidy provided to the project in the event of the sponsor's
or owner's fraud or willful non-compliance with respect to the requirements of this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The Board in its discretion may grant a waiver of any required remedial actions under this paragraph (e) for fraud
or willful non-compliance with respect to the requirements of this part, upon written request by the Bank, applicant,
loan fund or loan consortium, sponsor or owner. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart J_Required AHP Contributions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;960.18 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Required annual AHP contributions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each Bank shall fund its AHP in accordance with the following formula: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) In 1994, the greater of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 6 percent of the Bank's net earnings for the previous year; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) That Bank's 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
pro rata 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
share of an aggregate of $75 million to be contributed in total by the Banks, such proration being made on the basis of
the net earnings of the Banks for the previous year. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) In 1995 and each year thereafter, the greater of: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) 10 percent of the Bank's net earnings for the previous year; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) That Bank's 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
pro rata 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
share of an aggregate of $100 million to be contributed in total by the Banks, such proration being made on the basis
of the net earnings of the Banks for the previous year.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
