Subpart L_Advisory Councils 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;960.21 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Advisory Councils. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Appointment. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Each Bank shall appoint an Advisory Council of seven to 15 persons, as provided in the Bank's AHP implementation
plan. Advisory Council members shall reside in the Bank's district and shall be drawn from community and nonprofit
organizations actively involved in providing or promoting low- or moderate-income housing in the Bank's District.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Bank shall actively solicit nominations from Bank members and community and nonprofit organizations actively
involved in providing or promoting low- or moderate-income housing in the Bank's District, and shall allow sufficient
time for such organizations to respond, so that the nomination and appointment process is as broad and as participatory
as possible. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Advisory Council members shall be appointed by the Banks giving consideration to the size of the District and the
diversity of low-income housing needs within the District. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Advisory Council members shall serve for terms of two or three years, and such terms shall be staggered to provide
continuity and experience in service, as provided in the Bank's AHP implementation plan. An Advisory Council member
may not serve for more than six years consecutively. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) An Advisory Council member who, subsequent to appointment, is no longer employed by or associated with a community
or nonprofit organization actively involved in providing or promoting low- or moderate-income housing in the Bank's
District, may continue to serve on the Advisory Council until the end of his or her term. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Election of chairperson and vice chairperson. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each Advisory Council shall elect from among its voting members a chairperson and a vice chairperson. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Designation of secretary. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each Advisory Council shall designate a member, or request that a member of the Bank's staff be designated, to act as
secretary of the Advisory Council. The secretary shall record and maintain minutes of the meetings of the Advisory
Council. Minutes of each meeting shall contain, among other things, a record of the persons present, a description
of the matters discussed, and recommendations made. The person acting as secretary at a meeting shall certify to the
accuracy of the minutes of that meeting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Review of Bank's proposed AHP implementation plan and prior AHP applications. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Prior to approval of the Bank's proposed AHP implementation plan by the Bank's board of directors, the Bank's Advisory
Council shall review the proposed AHP implementation plan and provide its recommendations to the Bank's board of
directors pursuant to the requirements in &sect;960.2(c). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Upon request of the Advisory Council, the Bank shall provide the Advisory Council with copies of any AHP applications
from prior AHP funding cycles. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Meetings with the Banks. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Advisory Council shall meet with representatives of the board of directors of the Bank at least quarterly to advise
the Bank on low- and moderate-income housing programs and needs in the Bank's District and on the utilization of AHP
subsidized advances or direct subsidies for these purposes. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Report to the Board. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each Advisory Council shall submit to the Board annually by March 1 its analysis of the low-income housing activity
of its Bank. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Payment of expenses and compensation._
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Expenses. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each Bank shall reimburse members of its Advisory Council for transportation and subsistence expenses they incur
for each day devoted to attending quarterly meetings with representatives of the board of directors of the Bank. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Fees. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each Bank shall pay members of its Advisory Council a fee for each day devoted to attending quarterly meetings with
representatives of the board of directors of the Bank. 
