<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=15 g=1 f=3 -->
Section 392.40 All accidents.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 392.41 Striking unattended vehicle.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The FHWA is proposing to remove these two sections because they duplicate State ordinances. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=15 g=1 f=3 -->
Section 392.61 Driving by unauthorized person.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 392.62 Bus driver; distraction.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 392.65 Sleeper berth; transfer to or from.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 392.69 Sleeper berth, occupation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The FHWA is proposing to remove &sect;&sect;392.61 and 392.69 because the FHWA believes that these situations should
be governed by company policy or a labor management agreement. Section 392.62 duplicates State and local regulations
and should be removed. Section 392.65 is proposed to be removed because it is obsolete. There are very few truck tractors
still in use that require entry into the sleeper berth from outside the vehicle. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=3 -->
Part 396_Inspection, Repair, and Maintenance
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Part 396 places the responsibility upon the motor carrier to insure that its vehicles are properly maintained. The
FHWA is proposing to remove &sect;396.3(b)(4) because it is redundant. Section 396.3(b)(3) already requires motor
carriers to maintain for vehicles controlled for 30 consecutive days or more a record of inspection, repairs and maintenance
indicating their date and nature. Since the lubrication record required by &sect;396.3(b)(4) is a maintenance record,
the requirement is duplicative and should be removed.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=3 -->
Appendix A to Subchapter B
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Appendix A to subchapter B includes all interpretations that were issued by the FHWA up to the publication of a collection
of interpretations on November 23, 1977 (42 FR 60078). A new compilation of interpretations was recently published
in the 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Federal Register 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
on November 17, 1993 (58 FR 60734). Therefore, appendix A is redundant and obsolete, and the FHWA is proposing it be
removed. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

